EventItemActionText: This Land Use Application was Referred to Comm by Council to the Subcommittee on Landmarks, Public Siting and Maritime Uses

EventItemActionText: This Mayor's Message was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Communication for the Mayor - Mayor's veto and disapproval message of Introductory Number 226-A, in relation to requiring the police department and the department of education to provide the public with information regarding school violence.
EventItemMatterName: Mayor's Veto of Int 226-A, Provide the public with information regarding school violence.

EventItemActionText: This Mayor's Message was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Communication for the Mayor - Mayor's veto and disapproval message of Introductory Number 322-A, in relation to requiring the New York City Police Department to provide information to the City Council regarding school safety agents.
EventItemMatterName: Mayor's Veto of Int. 322-A, Requiring the NYPD and DOE to conduct an annual review and assessment of the need for school safety agents at each school operated by the DOE.
